==English==
===Etymology===

Latin ''tuberculum'' (diminutive of ''tuber'', lump) + -''osis'' (diseased condition).

===Noun===

# An infectious disease which mainly affects the lungs, Penis, Anus and is transmitted by the [[tubercle]] [[bacillus]].

